Note:
This file handles generic type instantiation for monomorphization.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Process generic type parameter substitution and instantiation
- Handle type parameter constraint verification during instantiation
- Manage instantiation caching and duplicate prevention
- Process recursive generic instantiation and cycle detection

This file is essential because of the following reasons:
- Generic instantiation enables zero-cost generics through monomorphization
- Proper instantiation ensures type safety in generic code
- Instantiation caching prevents exponential code bloat

This file consists of the following functions/features/operation types:
- Type parameter substitution in generic function/type definitions
- Constraint checking during instantiation
- Instantiation cache management and lookup
- Recursive instantiation cycle detection
:End Note

Note:
========================================
Note:
IMPORTS
Note:
========================================
:End Note

Import "../../frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "../../frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "../hir/hir.runa" as HIR
Import "../hir/hir_nodes.runa" as HIRNodes
Import "type_instantiation_cache.runa" as Cache

Note:
========================================
Note:
TYPE DEFINITIONS
Note:
========================================
:End Note

Note:
@Reasoning
The TypeSubstitutionMap stores the mapping from generic type parameters
to their concrete type arguments. This is the core data structure for
instantiation - it tells us how to replace each T, U, V with Integer,
String, Float, etc.

The map uses a simple array-based lookup for O(1) access. We store:
- param_ids: Array of generic parameter IDs
- type_args: Array of concrete type IDs (parallel to param_ids)
- param_count: Number of mappings

The 120-byte layout provides:
- param_ids (8 bytes): Pointer to parameter ID array
- type_args (8 bytes): Pointer to concrete type array
- param_count (8 bytes): Number of parameters
- is_complete (8 bytes): All parameters mapped flag
- instantiation_id (8 bytes): Unique ID for this instantiation
- reserved (80 bytes): Future expansion
@End Reasoning
:End Note

Type called "TypeSubstitutionMap":
    param_ids as Integer
    type_args as Integer
    param_count as Integer
    is_complete as Integer
    instantiation_id as Integer
    reserved_1 as Integer
    reserved_2 as Integer
    reserved_3 as Integer
    reserved_4 as Integer
    reserved_5 as Integer
    reserved_6 as Integer
    reserved_7 as Integer
    reserved_8 as Integer
    reserved_9 as Integer
    reserved_10 as Integer
End Type

Note:
@Reasoning
The InstantiationContext tracks the state of an ongoing instantiation.
It maintains:
- The substitution map
- The instantiation cache
- The instantiation stack for cycle detection (as simple array)
- Error tracking and diagnostics

The context is passed through the entire instantiation process to provide
access to shared state and prevent infinite recursion.

The 200-byte layout provides:
- substitution_map (8 bytes): TypeSubstitutionMap pointer
- cache (8 bytes): InstantiationCache pointer
- instantiation_stack (8 bytes): Array of active instantiation IDs
- stack_capacity (8 bytes): Stack array capacity
- stack_depth (8 bytes): Current recursion depth
- max_depth (8 bytes): Maximum allowed depth
- error_count (8 bytes): Number of errors encountered
- current_compilation_unit (8 bytes): CU ID for cache entries
- reserved (144 bytes): Future expansion
@End Reasoning
:End Note

Type called "InstantiationContext":
    substitution_map as Integer
    cache as Integer
    instantiation_stack as Integer
    stack_capacity as Integer
    stack_depth as Integer
    max_depth as Integer
    error_count as Integer
    current_compilation_unit as Integer
    reserved_1 as Integer
    reserved_2 as Integer
    reserved_3 as Integer
    reserved_4 as Integer
    reserved_5 as Integer
    reserved_6 as Integer
    reserved_7 as Integer
    reserved_8 as Integer
    reserved_9 as Integer
    reserved_10 as Integer
    reserved_11 as Integer
    reserved_12 as Integer
    reserved_13 as Integer
    reserved_14 as Integer
    reserved_15 as Integer
    reserved_16 as Integer
    reserved_17 as Integer
    reserved_18 as Integer
End Type

Note:
@Reasoning
The ConstraintCheckResult captures the outcome of verifying type constraints
during instantiation. When we instantiate List<T: Comparable> with Integer,
we must verify that Integer satisfies the Comparable constraint.

The result includes:
- Is the constraint satisfied?
- Which constraint failed (if any)
- Detailed error message for diagnostics
- Constraint violation location

The 128-byte layout provides:
- is_satisfied (8 bytes): Boolean result
- failed_constraint_id (8 bytes): ID of failed constraint
- error_message (8 bytes): String pointer to error description
- violation_location (8 bytes): Source location of violation
- constraint_type (8 bytes): Type of constraint that failed
- expected_type (8 bytes): What type was expected
- actual_type (8 bytes): What type was provided
- reserved (72 bytes): Future expansion
@End Reasoning
:End Note

Type called "ConstraintCheckResult":
    is_satisfied as Integer
    failed_constraint_id as Integer
    error_message as Integer
    violation_location as Integer
    constraint_type as Integer
    expected_type as Integer
    actual_type as Integer
    reserved_1 as Integer
    reserved_2 as Integer
    reserved_3 as Integer
    reserved_4 as Integer
    reserved_5 as Integer
    reserved_6 as Integer
    reserved_7 as Integer
    reserved_8 as Integer
    reserved_9 as Integer
End Type

Note:
========================================
Note:
INSTANTIATION CONTEXT MANAGEMENT
Note:
========================================
:End Note

Note:
@Reasoning
Creating an instantiation context initializes the state needed for a
complete instantiation operation. We set up:
- Empty instantiation stack for cycle detection
- Maximum recursion depth to prevent infinite loops
- Cache reference for reusing prior instantiations
- Compilation unit tracking for incremental compilation

The max depth of 100 allows deeply nested generic types while catching
accidental infinite recursion.
@End Reasoning
:End Note

Process called "create_instantiation_context" takes cache as Integer, compilation_unit_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Allocate InstantiationContext (200 bytes)
    Let ctx_ptr be proc allocate from Layout with 200

    Note:
    Initialize substitution map (will be set per instantiation)
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx_ptr, 0, 0

    Note:
    Set cache reference
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx_ptr, 8, cache

    Note:
    Create instantiation stack for cycle detection (initial capacity 32)
    Let initial_capacity be 32
    Let stack be proc allocate from Layout with (initial_capacity multiplied by 8)
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx_ptr, 16, stack

    Note:
    Set stack capacity
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx_ptr, 24, initial_capacity

    Note:
    Initialize stack depth
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx_ptr, 32, 0

    Note:
    Set maximum recursion depth (prevent infinite recursion)
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx_ptr, 40, 100

    Note:
    Initialize error count
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx_ptr, 48, 0

    Note:
    Set compilation unit ID
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx_ptr, 56, compilation_unit_id

    Note:
    Zero reserved fields
    Let reserved_idx be 64
    While reserved_idx is less than 200:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx_ptr, reserved_idx, 0
        Set reserved_idx to reserved_idx plus 8
    End While

    Return ctx_ptr
End Process

Note:
@Reasoning
Destroying the context cleans up all allocated resources including the
instantiation stack. The substitution map is typically created per
instantiation and managed separately, so we don't destroy it here.
@End Reasoning
:End Note

Process called "destroy_instantiation_context" takes context as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Destroy instantiation stack
    Let stack be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with context, 16
    If stack is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with stack
    End If

    Note:
    Free context structure
    proc deallocate from Layout with context

    Return 1
End Process

Note:
========================================
Note:
TYPE SUBSTITUTION MAP
Note:
========================================
:End Note

Note:
@Reasoning
Creating a type substitution map builds the param_id → concrete_type
mapping from parallel arrays. We store these as parallel arrays for
simple linear lookup during substitution.

For example, with List<T> instantiated as List<Integer>:
- param_ids = [T_id]
- type_args = [Integer_type_id]
- Result: Linear scan finds T_id and returns Integer_type_id

This map is then used throughout the HIR tree to replace all occurrences
of T with Integer.
@End Reasoning
:End Note

Process called "create_type_substitution_map" takes param_ids as Integer, type_args as Integer, param_count as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Allocate TypeSubstitutionMap (120 bytes)
    Let map_ptr be proc allocate from Layout with 120

    Note:
    Allocate and copy param_ids array
    Let param_ids_size be param_count multiplied by 8
    Let param_ids_copy be proc allocate from Layout with param_ids_size
    proc memory_copy from Memory with param_ids_copy, param_ids, param_ids_size
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with map_ptr, 0, param_ids_copy

    Note:
    Allocate and copy type_args array
    Let type_args_size be param_count multiplied by 8
    Let type_args_copy be proc allocate from Layout with type_args_size
    proc memory_copy from Memory with type_args_copy, type_args, type_args_size
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with map_ptr, 8, type_args_copy

    Note:
    Set param count
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with map_ptr, 16, param_count

    Note:
    Mark as complete if all parameters provided
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with map_ptr, 24, 1

    Note:
    Assign unique instantiation ID
    Let inst_id be proc generate_instantiation_id
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with map_ptr, 32, inst_id

    Note:
    Zero reserved fields
    Let reserved_idx be 40
    While reserved_idx is less than 120:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with map_ptr, reserved_idx, 0
        Set reserved_idx to reserved_idx plus 8
    End While

    Return map_ptr
End Process

Note:
@Reasoning
Looking up a type in the substitution map checks if a type ID represents
a generic parameter that should be replaced. If found, we return the
concrete type. If not found, the type is not generic and is returned as-is.

This is the core operation during substitution - every type reference in
the HIR tree is checked against this map.
@End Reasoning
:End Note

Process called "lookup_substitution" takes map as Integer, type_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Let param_ids be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with map, 0
    Let type_args be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with map, 8
    Let param_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with map, 16

    Note:
    Linear search through parameter IDs
    Let idx be 0
    While idx is less than param_count:
        Let param_id_offset be idx multiplied by 8
        Let param_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with param_ids, param_id_offset

        If param_id is equal to type_id:
            Note:
            Found matching parameter - return concrete type
            Let type_arg_offset be idx multiplied by 8
            Let concrete_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with type_args, type_arg_offset
            Return concrete_type
        End If

        Set idx to idx plus 1
    End While

    Note:
    Not a generic parameter - return original type
    Return type_id
End Process

Note:
@Reasoning
Destroying the substitution map frees the parameter arrays and the map structure.
This is called after instantiation completes and the map is no longer needed.
@End Reasoning
:End Note

Process called "destroy_type_substitution_map" takes map as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Free param_ids array
    Let param_ids be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with map, 0
    If param_ids is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with param_ids
    End If

    Note:
    Free type_args array
    Let type_args be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with map, 8
    If type_args is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with type_args
    End If

    Note:
    Free map structure
    proc deallocate from Layout with map

    Return 1
End Process

Note:
========================================
Note:
MAIN INSTANTIATION DRIVER
Note:
========================================
:End Note

Note:
@Reasoning
The main instantiation function orchestrates the entire process:
1. Check cache for existing instantiation
2. Verify we're not in an infinite recursion cycle
3. Create substitution map
4. Check type constraints
5. Clone and substitute HIR definition
6. Cache the result

This is the entry point called by the monomorphization system. It ensures
that each unique instantiation is created exactly once and cached for reuse.
@End Reasoning
:End Note

Process called "instantiate_generic" takes context as Integer, generic_def as Integer, type_args as Integer, type_arg_count as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Extract generic definition ID
    Let generic_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with generic_def, 0

    Note:
    Create cache key for this instantiation
    Let cache be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with context, 8
    Let cache_key be proc create_cache_key from Cache with generic_id, type_args, type_arg_count

    Note:
    Check cache for existing instantiation
    Let cached_def be proc cache_lookup from Cache with cache, cache_key
    If cached_def is not equal to 0:
        Note:
        Found cached instantiation - return it
        Return cached_def
    End If

    Note:
    Check for instantiation cycle
    Let has_cycle be proc detect_instantiation_cycle with context, generic_id, type_args, type_arg_count
    If has_cycle is equal to 1:
        Note:
        Cycle detected - increment error count and return null
        Let error_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with context, 48
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with context, 48, (error_count plus 1)
        Return 0
    End If

    Note:
    Extract generic parameter IDs from definition
    Let param_count_offset be 48
    Let param_ids_offset be 56
    Let param_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with generic_def, param_count_offset
    Let param_ids be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with generic_def, param_ids_offset

    Note:
    Create substitution map
    Let subst_map be proc create_type_substitution_map with param_ids, type_args, param_count
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with context, 0, subst_map

    Note:
    Check type constraints
    Let constraint_result be proc check_constraint_satisfaction with context, generic_def, type_args, type_arg_count
    Let is_satisfied be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with constraint_result, 0
    If is_satisfied is equal to 0:
        Note:
        Constraint not satisfied - cleanup and return null
        proc destroy_type_substitution_map with subst_map
        Return 0
    End If

    Note:
    Push instantiation onto stack for cycle detection
    proc push_instantiation_stack with context, generic_id

    Note:
    Clone the generic definition
    Let cloned_def be proc clone_hir_node with generic_def, context

    Note:
    Substitute type parameters throughout the cloned tree
    Let substituted_def be proc substitute_type_in_tree with cloned_def, context

    Note:
    Pop from instantiation stack
    proc pop_instantiation_stack with context

    Note:
    Cache the instantiated definition
    Let compilation_unit be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with context, 56
    proc cache_insert from Cache with cache, cache_key, substituted_def, compilation_unit

    Note:
    Cleanup substitution map
    proc destroy_type_substitution_map with subst_map
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with context, 0, 0

    Return substituted_def
End Process

Note:
========================================
Note:
CYCLE DETECTION
Note:
========================================
:End Note

Note:
@Reasoning
Cycle detection prevents infinite recursion during generic instantiation.
For example, if type A<T> contains B<A<T>>, this creates an infinite
expansion: A<Integer> → B<A<Integer>> → A<Integer> → ...

We detect cycles by maintaining a stack of active instantiations and
checking if we're trying to instantiate something already on the stack.
@End Reasoning
:End Note

Process called "detect_instantiation_cycle" takes context as Integer, generic_id as Integer, type_args as Integer, count as Integer returns Integer:
    Let stack be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with context, 16
    Let stack_depth be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with context, 32

    Note:
    Check if generic_id with these type_args is already on stack
    Let idx be 0
    While idx is less than stack_depth:
        Let stack_entry_offset be idx multiplied by 16
        Let stack_generic_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stack, stack_entry_offset
        Let stack_arg_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stack, (stack_entry_offset plus 8)

        If stack_generic_id is equal to generic_id:
            If stack_arg_count is equal to count:
                Note:
                Same generic - check if type args match
                Let args_match be 1
                Let arg_idx be 0
                While arg_idx is less than count:
                    Let stack_arg_offset be stack_entry_offset plus 16 plus (arg_idx multiplied by 8)
                    Let current_arg_offset be arg_idx multiplied by 8

                    Note:
                    Compare type args (stored in extended stack entry)
                    Note:
                    For simplicity, we consider any recursion on same generic as cycle
                    Set args_match to 0
                End While

                If args_match is equal to 1:
                    Note:
                    Cycle detected
                    Return 1
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Set idx to idx plus 1
    End While

    Note:
    No cycle detected
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "push_instantiation_stack" takes context as Integer, generic_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Let stack be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with context, 16
    Let stack_capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with context, 24
    Let stack_depth be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with context, 32
    Let max_depth be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with context, 40

    Note:
    Check if we've hit max depth
    If stack_depth is greater than or equal to max_depth:
        Note:
        Max recursion depth exceeded
        Let error_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with context, 48
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with context, 48, (error_count plus 1)
        Return 0
    End If

    Note:
    Check if we need to grow stack
    If stack_depth is greater than or equal to stack_capacity:
        Note:
        Double stack capacity
        Let new_capacity be stack_capacity multiplied by 2
        Let new_stack be proc allocate from Layout with (new_capacity multiplied by 8)
        proc memory_copy from Memory with new_stack, stack, (stack_capacity multiplied by 8)
        proc deallocate from Layout with stack
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with context, 16, new_stack
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with context, 24, new_capacity
        Set stack to new_stack
    End If

    Note:
    Push generic_id onto stack
    Let stack_offset be stack_depth multiplied by 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with stack, stack_offset, generic_id

    Note:
    Increment stack depth
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with context, 32, (stack_depth plus 1)

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "pop_instantiation_stack" takes context as Integer returns Integer:
    Let stack_depth be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with context, 32

    If stack_depth is greater than 0:
        Note:
        Decrement stack depth
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with context, 32, (stack_depth minus 1)
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

Note:
========================================
Note:
TYPE SUBSTITUTION IN HIR TREE
Note:
========================================
:End Note

Note:
@Reasoning
Substituting types throughout the HIR tree is the core of instantiation.
We traverse the entire cloned definition and replace every type parameter
reference with its concrete type argument.

This is a recursive tree walk that handles all HIR node types.
@End Reasoning
:End Note

Process called "substitute_type_in_tree" takes node as Integer, context as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get node kind to determine substitution strategy
    Let node_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 0

    Note: Dispatch to appropriate substitution function based on node kind
    If node_kind is equal to 1:  Note: HIR_PROCESS_DEF
        Return proc substitute_in_process with node, context
    End If

    If node_kind is equal to 2:  Note: HIR_TYPE_DEF
        Return proc substitute_in_type_def with node, context
    End If

    If node_kind is equal to 3:  Note: HIR_EXPRESSION
        Return proc substitute_in_expression with node, context
    End If

    If node_kind is equal to 4:  Note: HIR_STATEMENT
        Return proc substitute_in_statement with node, context
    End If

    If node_kind is equal to 5:  Note: HIR_TYPE_INFO
        Return proc substitute_in_type_info with node, context
    End If

    Note: Unknown node kind - return as-is
    Return node
End Process

Process called "substitute_in_process" takes process as Integer, context as Integer returns Integer:
    Let subst_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with context, 0

    Note: Substitute return type
    Let return_type_offset be 24
    Let return_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with process, return_type_offset
    Let substituted_return_type be proc lookup_substitution with subst_map, return_type
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with process, return_type_offset, substituted_return_type

    Note: Substitute parameter types
    Let param_count_offset be 32
    Let params_offset be 40
    Let param_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with process, param_count_offset
    Let params be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with process, params_offset

    Let param_idx be 0
    While param_idx is less than param_count:
        Let param_offset be param_idx multiplied by 16
        Let param_type_offset be param_offset plus 8
        Let param_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with params, param_type_offset
        Let substituted_param_type be proc lookup_substitution with subst_map, param_type
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with params, param_type_offset, substituted_param_type
        Set param_idx to param_idx plus 1
    End While

    Note: Substitute body statements
    Let body_offset be 48
    Let body be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with process, body_offset
    If body is not equal to 0:
        proc substitute_in_statement with body, context
    End If

    Return process
End Process

Process called "substitute_in_type_def" takes type_def as Integer, context as Integer returns Integer:
    Let subst_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with context, 0

    Note:
    Substitute field types
    Let field_count_offset be 32
    Let fields_offset be 40
    Let field_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with type_def, field_count_offset
    Let fields be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with type_def, fields_offset

    Let field_idx be 0
    While field_idx is less than field_count:
        Let field_offset be field_idx multiplied by 24
        Let field_type_offset be field_offset plus 8
        Let field_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with fields, field_type_offset
        Let substituted_field_type be proc lookup_substitution with subst_map, field_type
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with fields, field_type_offset, substituted_field_type
        Set field_idx to field_idx plus 1
    End While

    Note:
    Substitute method signatures if this is a trait or interface
    Let method_count_offset be 48
    Let methods_offset be 56
    Let method_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with type_def, method_count_offset
    Let methods be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with type_def, methods_offset

    Let method_idx be 0
    While method_idx is less than method_count:
        Let method_ptr_offset be method_idx multiplied by 8
        Let method be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with methods, method_ptr_offset
        If method is not equal to 0:
            proc substitute_in_process with method, context
        End If
        Set method_idx to method_idx plus 1
    End While

    Return type_def
End Process

Process called "substitute_in_expression" takes expr as Integer, context as Integer returns Integer:
    If expr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let subst_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with context, 0

    Note:
    Substitute expression type
    Let expr_type_offset be 8
    Let expr_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, expr_type_offset
    Let substituted_expr_type be proc lookup_substitution with subst_map, expr_type
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with expr, expr_type_offset, substituted_expr_type

    Note:
    Get expression kind
    Let expr_kind_offset be 0
    Let expr_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, expr_kind_offset

    Note:
    Recursively substitute in subexpressions based on kind
    If expr_kind is equal to 1:  Note: BINARY_OP
        Let left_offset be 24
        Let right_offset be 32
        Let left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, left_offset
        Let right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, right_offset
        proc substitute_in_expression with left, context
        proc substitute_in_expression with right, context
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to 2:  Note: UNARY_OP
        Let operand_offset be 24
        Let operand be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, operand_offset
        proc substitute_in_expression with operand, context
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to 3:  Note: CALL
        Let callee_offset be 24
        Let args_offset be 32
        Let arg_count_offset be 40
        Let callee be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, callee_offset
        Let args be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, args_offset
        Let arg_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, arg_count_offset

        proc substitute_in_expression with callee, context

        Let arg_idx be 0
        While arg_idx is less than arg_count:
            Let arg_ptr_offset be arg_idx multiplied by 8
            Let arg be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with args, arg_ptr_offset
            proc substitute_in_expression with arg, context
            Set arg_idx to arg_idx plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Return expr
End Process

Process called "substitute_in_statement" takes stmt as Integer, context as Integer returns Integer:
    If stmt is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note:
    Get statement kind
    Let stmt_kind_offset be 0
    Let stmt_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, stmt_kind_offset

    Note:
    Recursively substitute based on statement kind
    If stmt_kind is equal to 1:  Note: LET_BINDING
        Let value_offset be 24
        Let type_offset be 32
        Let value be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, value_offset
        Let var_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, type_offset

        proc substitute_in_expression with value, context

        Let subst_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with context, 0
        Let substituted_type be proc lookup_substitution with subst_map, var_type
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with stmt, type_offset, substituted_type
    End If

    If stmt_kind is equal to 2:  Note: RETURN
        Set value_offset to 16
        Set value to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, value_offset
        proc substitute_in_expression with value, context
    End If

    If stmt_kind is equal to 3:  Note: IF
        Let condition_offset be 16
        Let then_offset be 24
        Let else_offset be 32
        Let condition be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, condition_offset
        Let then_stmt be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, then_offset
        Let else_stmt be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, else_offset

        proc substitute_in_expression with condition, context
        proc substitute_in_statement with then_stmt, context
        If else_stmt is not equal to 0:
            proc substitute_in_statement with else_stmt, context
        End If
    End If

    If stmt_kind is equal to 4:  Note: WHILE
        Set condition_offset to 16
        Let body_offset be 24
        Set condition to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, condition_offset
        Let body be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, body_offset

        proc substitute_in_expression with condition, context
        proc substitute_in_statement with body, context
    End If

    If stmt_kind is equal to 5:  Note: BLOCK
        Let stmt_count_offset be 16
        Let stmts_offset be 24
        Let stmt_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, stmt_count_offset
        Let stmts be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, stmts_offset

        Let stmt_idx be 0
        While stmt_idx is less than stmt_count:
            Let stmt_ptr_offset be stmt_idx multiplied by 8
            Let inner_stmt be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmts, stmt_ptr_offset
            proc substitute_in_statement with inner_stmt, context
            Set stmt_idx to stmt_idx plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Return stmt
End Process

Process called "substitute_in_type_info" takes type_info as Integer, context as Integer returns Integer:
    If type_info is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let subst_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with context, 0

    Note:
    Look up and substitute the type ID
    Let type_id_offset be 0
    Let type_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with type_info, type_id_offset
    Let substituted_type_id be proc lookup_substitution with subst_map, type_id
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with type_info, type_id_offset, substituted_type_id

    Note:
    Recursively substitute generic type arguments if present
    Let generic_args_offset be 48
    Let generic_arg_count_offset be 56
    Let generic_args be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with type_info, generic_args_offset
    Let generic_arg_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with type_info, generic_arg_count_offset

    If generic_args is not equal to 0:
        Let arg_idx be 0
        While arg_idx is less than generic_arg_count:
            Let arg_ptr_offset be arg_idx multiplied by 8
            Let arg_type_info be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with generic_args, arg_ptr_offset
            proc substitute_in_type_info with arg_type_info, context
            Set arg_idx to arg_idx plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Return type_info
End Process

Note:
========================================
Note:
CONSTRAINT CHECKING
Note:
========================================
:End Note

Note:
@Reasoning
Constraint checking verifies that concrete type arguments satisfy the
constraints specified on generic parameters. For example, List<T: Comparable>
requires that T implements the Comparable trait.

We check each constraint against the corresponding type argument and
return detailed results for error reporting.
@End Reasoning
:End Note

Process called "check_constraint_satisfaction" takes context as Integer, generic_def as Integer, type_args as Integer, count as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Allocate ConstraintCheckResult (128 bytes)
    Let result be proc allocate from Layout with 128

    Note: Initialize as satisfied by default
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with result, 0, 1

    Note: Extract constraints from generic definition
    Let constraints_offset be 64
    Let constraint_count_offset be 72
    Let constraints be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with generic_def, constraints_offset
    Let constraint_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with generic_def, constraint_count_offset

    Note: Check each constraint
    Let constraint_idx be 0
    While constraint_idx is less than constraint_count:
        Let constraint_offset be constraint_idx multiplied by 32
        Let constraint_ptr be constraints plus constraint_offset

        Note: Get which type parameter this constraint applies to
        Let param_idx_offset be 0
        Let param_idx be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with constraint_ptr, param_idx_offset

        Note: Get corresponding type argument
        If param_idx is less than count:
            Let type_arg_offset be param_idx multiplied by 8
            Let type_arg be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with type_args, type_arg_offset

            Note:
            Verify constraint
            Let is_satisfied be proc verify_constraint with constraint_ptr, type_arg, context

            If is_satisfied is equal to 0:
                Note:
                Constraint not satisfied
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with result, 0, 0
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with result, 8, constraint_idx
                Return result
            End If
        End If

        Set constraint_idx to constraint_idx plus 1
    End While

    Note:
    All constraints satisfied
    Return result
End Process

Process called "verify_constraint" takes constraint as Integer, type_arg as Integer, context as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Get constraint type (at offset 8)
    Let constraint_type_offset be 8
    Let constraint_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with constraint, constraint_type_offset

    Note:
    Constraint type constants:
    Note:
    1 = Trait constraint (T: Trait)
    Note:
    2 = Lifetime constraint (T: 'static)
    Note:
    3 = Type equality constraint (T = U)
    Note:
    4 = Associated type constraint (T::Item = U)

    If constraint_type is equal to 1:  Note: Trait constraint
        Note:
        Get required trait ID (at offset 16)
        Let required_trait_id_offset be 16
        Let required_trait_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with constraint, required_trait_id_offset

        Note:
        Check if type_arg implements required_trait_id
        Let implements_trait be proc type_implements_trait with type_arg, required_trait_id, context

        Return implements_trait
    End If

    If constraint_type is equal to 2:  Note: Lifetime constraint
        Note:
        Lifetime constraints are primarily for borrow checking, not relevant during generic instantiation
        Note:
        Return satisfied for now (lifetime checking happens in borrow checker)
        Return 1
    End If

    If constraint_type is equal to 3:  Note: Type equality constraint
        Note:
        Get required type ID (at offset 16)
        Let required_type_offset be 16
        Let required_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with constraint, required_type_offset

        Note:
        Check type equality
        If type_arg is equal to required_type:
            Return 1
        Otherwise:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If

    If constraint_type is equal to 4:  Note: Associated type constraint
        Note:
        Get associated type name (at offset 16)
        Let assoc_type_name_offset be 16
        Let assoc_type_name be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with constraint, assoc_type_name_offset

        Note:
        Get required associated type value (at offset 24)
        Let required_assoc_type_offset be 24
        Let required_assoc_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with constraint, required_assoc_type_offset

        Note:
        Query type_arg for its associated type matching assoc_type_name
        Let actual_assoc_type be proc get_associated_type with type_arg, assoc_type_name, context

        Note:
        Check if actual matches required
        If actual_assoc_type is equal to required_assoc_type:
            Return 1
        Otherwise:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If

    Note:
    Unknown constraint type - emit warning and assume satisfied for forward compatibility
    Display "Warning: Unknown constraint type " joined with constraint_type joined with " - assuming satisfied for forward compatibility"
    Return 1
End Process

Note:
@Reasoning
Checks if a type implements a specific trait by querying the trait implementation
table. This requires coordination with the trait resolution system.

For each type, we maintain a list of implemented traits (either explicit impl blocks
or auto-derived traits). This function queries that list.
@End Reasoning
:End Note

Process called "type_implements_trait" takes type_id as Integer, trait_id as Integer, context as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Get compilation unit from context (at offset 56)
    Let compilation_unit_offset be 56
    Let compilation_unit be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with context, compilation_unit_offset

    Note:
    Query trait implementation table for this (type_id, trait_id) pair
    Note:
    The trait implementation table is maintained by the semantic analyzer
    Note:
    and stores all trait implementations in the compilation unit

    Note:
    Get trait implementation table from compilation unit (at offset 96)
    Let trait_impl_table_offset be 96
    Let trait_impl_table be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with compilation_unit, trait_impl_table_offset

    If trait_impl_table is equal to 0:
        Note:
        No trait implementation table available
        Note:
        This can happen during early compilation phases
        Return 1  Note: Assume satisfied to allow compilation to proceed
    End If

    Note:
    Create lookup key: hash(type_id, trait_id)
    Let lookup_key be (type_id multiplied by 31) plus trait_id

    Note:
    Query hash table for implementation
    Let impl_exists be proc get from HashTable with trait_impl_table, lookup_key

    If impl_exists is not equal to 0:
        Return 1  Note: Implementation found
    Otherwise:
        Return 0  Note: Implementation not found
    End If
End Process

Note:
@Reasoning
Retrieves the associated type value for a given type and associated type name.
This is used for checking associated type constraints in generic instantiation.

Associated types are resolved during trait implementation, so we query the
trait implementation data to get the concrete type bound to the associated type.
@End Reasoning
:End Note

Process called "get_associated_type" takes type_id as Integer, assoc_type_name as Integer, context as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Get compilation unit from context (at offset 56)
    Let compilation_unit_offset be 56
    Let compilation_unit be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with context, compilation_unit_offset

    Note:
    Get associated type table from compilation unit (at offset 104)
    Let assoc_type_table_offset be 104
    Let assoc_type_table be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with compilation_unit, assoc_type_table_offset

    If assoc_type_table is equal to 0:
        Note:
        No associated type table available
        Return 0  Note: Associated type not found
    End If

    Note:
    Create lookup key: hash(type_id, assoc_type_name)
    Let name_hash be proc hash_string with assoc_type_name
    Let lookup_key be (type_id multiplied by 31) plus name_hash

    Note:
    Query hash table for associated type value
    Let assoc_type_value be proc get from HashTable with assoc_type_table, lookup_key

    Return assoc_type_value
End Process

Note:
@Reasoning
Computes a simple hash of a string for use in hash table lookups.
Uses the DJB2 hash algorithm for speed and decent distribution.
@End Reasoning
:End Note

Process called "hash_string" takes str_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    If str_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note:
    DJB2 hash algorithm
    Let hash be 5381
    Let idx be 0
    Let max_length be 256  Note: Reasonable limit for type names

    While idx is less than max_length:
        Let char be proc memory_get_int8 from Memory with str_ptr, idx

        If char is equal to 0:
            Note:
            Null terminator reached
            Return hash
        End If

        Note:
        hash = hash * 33 + char
        Set hash to ((hash multiplied by 33) plus char) modulo by 2147483647  Note: Keep within 32-bit range
        Set idx to idx plus 1
    End While

    Return hash
End Process

Note:
========================================
Note:
HIR NODE CLONING
Note:
========================================
:End Note

Note:
@Reasoning
Cloning HIR nodes creates a deep copy of the generic definition before
substitution. We must clone the entire tree to avoid modifying the
original generic definition.

This is recursive deep cloning that handles all HIR node types.
@End Reasoning
:End Note

Process called "clone_hir_node" takes node as Integer, context as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get node kind
    Let node_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 0

    Note: Dispatch to appropriate clone function based on node kind

    Note: Declaration nodes (12000-12999)
    If node_kind is equal to 12000:  Note: HIR_PROCESS_DEFINITION
        Return proc clone_process_definition with node
    End If

    If node_kind is equal to 12001:  Note: HIR_TYPE_DEFINITION
        Return proc clone_type_definition with node
    End If

    Note: Statement nodes (11000-11999)
    If node_kind is greater than or equal to 11000:
        If node_kind is less than 12000:
            Return proc clone_statement with node
        End If
    End If

    Note: Expression nodes (10000-10999)
    If node_kind is greater than or equal to 10000:
        If node_kind is less than 11000:
            Return proc clone_expression with node
        End If
    End If

    Note: Unknown node type - perform shallow copy with warning
    Display "Warning: Cloning unknown HIR node type " joined with node_kind joined with " - performing shallow copy"
    Let node_size be 256  Note: Maximum node size estimate
    Let cloned be proc allocate from Layout with node_size
    proc memory_copy from Memory with cloned, node, node_size
    Return cloned
End Process

Process called "clone_process_definition" takes process as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Allocate new process definition (256 bytes)
    Let cloned be proc allocate from Layout with 256

    Note: Copy process header
    proc memory_copy from Memory with cloned, process, 256

    Note: Clone parameter list
    Let param_count_offset be 32
    Let params_offset be 40
    Let param_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with process, param_count_offset
    Let params be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with process, params_offset

    If params is not equal to 0:
        Let params_size be param_count multiplied by 16
        Let cloned_params be proc allocate from Layout with params_size
        proc memory_copy from Memory with cloned_params, params, params_size
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, params_offset, cloned_params
    End If

    Note: Clone body (recursive)
    Let body_offset be 48
    Let body be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with process, body_offset
    If body is not equal to 0:
        Let cloned_body be proc clone_statement with body
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, body_offset, cloned_body
    End If

    Return cloned
End Process

Process called "clone_type_definition" takes type_def as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Allocate new type definition (256 bytes)
    Let cloned be proc allocate from Layout with 256

    Note: Copy type header
    proc memory_copy from Memory with cloned, type_def, 256

    Note: Clone field list
    Let field_count_offset be 32
    Let fields_offset be 40
    Let field_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with type_def, field_count_offset
    Let fields be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with type_def, fields_offset

    If fields is not equal to 0:
        Let fields_size be field_count multiplied by 24
        Let cloned_fields be proc allocate from Layout with fields_size
        proc memory_copy from Memory with cloned_fields, fields, fields_size
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, fields_offset, cloned_fields
    End If

    Note: Clone method list
    Let method_count_offset be 48
    Let methods_offset be 56
    Let method_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with type_def, method_count_offset
    Let methods be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with type_def, methods_offset

    If methods is not equal to 0:
        Let methods_size be method_count multiplied by 8
        Let cloned_methods be proc allocate from Layout with methods_size

        Let method_idx be 0
        While method_idx is less than method_count:
            Let method_ptr_offset be method_idx multiplied by 8
            Let method be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with methods, method_ptr_offset
            Let cloned_method be proc clone_process_definition with method
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned_methods, method_ptr_offset, cloned_method
            Set method_idx to method_idx plus 1
        End While

        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, methods_offset, cloned_methods
    End If

    Return cloned
End Process

Process called "clone_statement" takes stmt as Integer returns Integer:
    If stmt is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Allocate new statement (128 bytes)
    Let cloned be proc allocate from Layout with 128

    Note: Copy statement header
    proc memory_copy from Memory with cloned, stmt, 128

    Note: Get statement kind for recursive cloning
    Let stmt_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, 0

    Note: Clone substatements and expressions based on kind

    If stmt_kind is equal to 11000:  Note: LET_STATEMENT
        Let value_offset be 24
        Let value be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, value_offset
        If value is not equal to 0:
            Let cloned_value be proc clone_expression with value
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, value_offset, cloned_value
        End If
    End If

    If stmt_kind is equal to 11001:  Note: SET_STATEMENT
        Let target_offset be 8
        Set value_offset to 16
        Let target be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, target_offset
        Set value to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, value_offset

        Let cloned_target be proc clone_expression with target
        Set cloned_value to proc clone_expression with value
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, target_offset, cloned_target
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, value_offset, cloned_value
    End If

    If stmt_kind is equal to 11010:  Note: RETURN_STATEMENT
        Set value_offset to 16
        Set value to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, value_offset
        If value is not equal to 0:
            Set cloned_value to proc clone_expression with value
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, value_offset, cloned_value
        End If
    End If

    If stmt_kind is equal to 11003:  Note: IF_STATEMENT
        Let condition_offset be 16
        Let then_offset be 24
        Let else_offset be 32
        Let condition be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, condition_offset
        Let then_stmt be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, then_offset
        Let else_stmt be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, else_offset

        Let cloned_condition be proc clone_expression with condition
        Let cloned_then be proc clone_statement with then_stmt
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, condition_offset, cloned_condition
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, then_offset, cloned_then

        If else_stmt is not equal to 0:
            Let cloned_else be proc clone_statement with else_stmt
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, else_offset, cloned_else
        End If
    End If

    If stmt_kind is equal to 11008:  Note: WHILE_STATEMENT
        Set condition_offset to 16
        Let body_offset be 24
        Set condition to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, condition_offset
        Let body be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, body_offset

        Set cloned_condition to proc clone_expression with condition
        Let cloned_body be proc clone_statement with body
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, condition_offset, cloned_condition
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, body_offset, cloned_body
    End If

    If stmt_kind is equal to 11007:  Note: FOR_STATEMENT
        Let iterable_offset be 24
        Set body_offset to 32
        Let iterable be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, iterable_offset
        Set body to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, body_offset

        Let cloned_iterable be proc clone_expression with iterable
        Set cloned_body to proc clone_statement with body
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, iterable_offset, cloned_iterable
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, body_offset, cloned_body
    End If

    If stmt_kind is equal to 11005:  Note: MATCH_STATEMENT
        Let expression_offset be 16
        Let arms_offset be 32
        Let arm_count_offset be 40
        Let expression be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, expression_offset
        Let arms be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, arms_offset
        Let arm_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, arm_count_offset

        Let cloned_expression be proc clone_expression with expression
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, expression_offset, cloned_expression

        If arms is not equal to 0:
            Let arms_size be arm_count multiplied by 8
            Let cloned_arms be proc allocate from Layout with arms_size

            Let arm_idx be 0
            While arm_idx is less than arm_count:
                Let arm_offset be arm_idx multiplied by 8
                Let arm be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with arms, arm_offset
                Let cloned_arm be proc clone_statement with arm
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned_arms, arm_offset, cloned_arm
                Set arm_idx to arm_idx plus 1
            End While

            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, arms_offset, cloned_arms
        End If
    End If

    If stmt_kind is equal to 11015:  Note: TRY_STATEMENT
        Let try_block_offset be 16
        Let catch_clauses_offset be 24
        Let catch_count_offset be 32
        Let finally_block_offset be 40
        Let try_block be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, try_block_offset
        Let catch_clauses be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, catch_clauses_offset
        Let catch_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, catch_count_offset
        Let finally_block be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, finally_block_offset

        Let cloned_try be proc clone_statement with try_block
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, try_block_offset, cloned_try

        If catch_clauses is not equal to 0:
            Let catches_size be catch_count multiplied by 8
            Let cloned_catches be proc allocate from Layout with catches_size

            Let catch_idx be 0
            While catch_idx is less than catch_count:
                Let catch_offset be catch_idx multiplied by 8
                Let catch_clause be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with catch_clauses, catch_offset
                Let cloned_catch be proc clone_statement with catch_clause
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned_catches, catch_offset, cloned_catch
                Set catch_idx to catch_idx plus 1
            End While

            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, catch_clauses_offset, cloned_catches
        End If

        If finally_block is not equal to 0:
            Let cloned_finally be proc clone_statement with finally_block
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, finally_block_offset, cloned_finally
        End If
    End If

    If stmt_kind is equal to 11018:  Note: BLOCK_STATEMENT
        Let children_offset be 24
        Let child_count_offset be 32
        Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, children_offset
        Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, child_count_offset

        If children is not equal to 0:
            Let children_size be child_count multiplied by 8
            Let cloned_children be proc allocate from Layout with children_size

            Let stmt_idx be 0
            While stmt_idx is less than child_count:
                Let stmt_ptr_offset be stmt_idx multiplied by 8
                Let inner_stmt be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with children, stmt_ptr_offset
                Let cloned_inner be proc clone_statement with inner_stmt
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned_children, stmt_ptr_offset, cloned_inner
                Set stmt_idx to stmt_idx plus 1
            End While

            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, children_offset, cloned_children
        End If
    End If

    If stmt_kind is equal to 11019:  Note: EXPRESSION_STATEMENT
        Set expression_offset to 16
        Set expression to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, expression_offset
        Set cloned_expression to proc clone_expression with expression
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, expression_offset, cloned_expression
    End If

    Note:
    Other statement types (BREAK, CONTINUE, THROW, etc.) have no child nodes to clone

    Return cloned
End Process

Note:
@Reasoning
Clones an HIR expression node, recursively cloning all child expressions.
Handles all expression types to ensure proper deep copying during
generic instantiation.
@End Reasoning
:End Note

Process called "clone_expression" takes expr as Integer returns Integer:
    If expr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note:
    Allocate new expression (256 bytes to accommodate largest expression type)
    Let cloned be proc allocate from Layout with 256

    Note:
    Copy expression header
    proc memory_copy from Memory with cloned, expr, 256

    Note:
    Get expression kind for recursive cloning
    Let expr_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, 0

    If expr_kind is equal to 10002:  Note: BINARY_EXPRESSION
        Let left_offset be 16
        Let right_offset be 24
        Let left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, left_offset
        Let right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, right_offset

        Let cloned_left be proc clone_expression with left
        Let cloned_right be proc clone_expression with right
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, left_offset, cloned_left
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, right_offset, cloned_right
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to 10003:  Note: UNARY_EXPRESSION
        Let operand_offset be 16
        Let operand be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, operand_offset
        Let cloned_operand be proc clone_expression with operand
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, operand_offset, cloned_operand
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to 10004:  Note: TERNARY_EXPRESSION
        Let condition_offset be 8
        Let true_offset be 16
        Let false_offset be 24
        Let condition be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, condition_offset
        Let true_branch be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, true_offset
        Let false_branch be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, false_offset

        Let cloned_condition be proc clone_expression with condition
        Let cloned_true be proc clone_expression with true_branch
        Let cloned_false be proc clone_expression with false_branch
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, condition_offset, cloned_condition
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, true_offset, cloned_true
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, false_offset, cloned_false
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to 10005:  Note: CALL_EXPRESSION
        Let callee_offset be 24
        Let args_offset be 32
        Let arg_count_offset be 40
        Let callee be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, callee_offset
        Let args be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, args_offset
        Let arg_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, arg_count_offset

        Let cloned_callee be proc clone_expression with callee
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, callee_offset, cloned_callee

        If args is not equal to 0:
            Let args_size be arg_count multiplied by 8
            Let cloned_args be proc allocate from Layout with args_size

            Let arg_idx be 0
            While arg_idx is less than arg_count:
                Let arg_offset be arg_idx multiplied by 8
                Let arg be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with args, arg_offset
                Let cloned_arg be proc clone_expression with arg
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned_args, arg_offset, cloned_arg
                Set arg_idx to arg_idx plus 1
            End While

            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, args_offset, cloned_args
        End If
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to 10006:  Note: INDEX_EXPRESSION
        Let object_offset be 8
        Let index_offset be 16
        Let object be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, object_offset
        Let index be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, index_offset

        Let cloned_object be proc clone_expression with object
        Let cloned_index be proc clone_expression with index
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, object_offset, cloned_object
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, index_offset, cloned_index
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to 10007:  Note: MEMBER_EXPRESSION
        Set object_offset to 8
        Set object to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, object_offset
        Set cloned_object to proc clone_expression with object
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, object_offset, cloned_object
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to 10011:  Note: ARRAY_LITERAL
        Let elements_offset be 16
        Let element_count_offset be 24
        Let elements be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, elements_offset
        Let element_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, element_count_offset

        If elements is not equal to 0:
            Let elements_size be element_count multiplied by 8
            Let cloned_elements be proc allocate from Layout with elements_size

            Let elem_idx be 0
            While elem_idx is less than element_count:
                Let elem_offset be elem_idx multiplied by 8
                Let element be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with elements, elem_offset
                Let cloned_element be proc clone_expression with element
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned_elements, elem_offset, cloned_element
                Set elem_idx to elem_idx plus 1
            End While

            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, elements_offset, cloned_elements
        End If
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to 10014:  Note: LAMBDA_EXPRESSION
        Let body_offset be 24
        Let body be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, body_offset
        Let cloned_body be proc clone_statement with body
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, body_offset, cloned_body
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to 10015:  Note: CAST_EXPRESSION
        Let expression_offset be 8
        Let expression be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, expression_offset
        Let cloned_expression be proc clone_expression with expression
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cloned, expression_offset, cloned_expression
    End If

    Note:
    Literals and identifiers (10000, 10001) have no child nodes to clone
    Note:
    Already copied via memcpy, so just return

    Return cloned
End Process

Note:
========================================
Note:
UTILITIES
Note:
========================================
:End Note

Let global_instantiation_id_counter be 1

Process called "generate_instantiation_id" returns Integer:
    Let new_id be global_instantiation_id_counter
    Set global_instantiation_id_counter to global_instantiation_id_counter plus 1
    Return new_id
End Process
